 But with strong cash positions\nand heavier traffic fairly confidently\nforecast for the last half of the year\nreductions in disbursements are not\nexpected.\nPresidents Donnelly of the Northern\nPacific and Williamson of the Burling\nton reported fairly good crop conditions\nIn their territories, but few signs of\nbusiness improvement. The Philadel\nphia Federal Reserve Bank veported an\nincrease of about 2 per cent in employ\nment in the anthracite coal fields in\nApril over March, but a drop of 18\nper cent from April. 1929. The Ouar\nanty Trust Co., in its monthly survey\nof business, found conditions practically\nunchanged and pointed to unsettled\ncommodity prices and a high level of\nbusiness failures as deterrents to im\nprovement. it stated, however, that\nthe Summer seasonal contraction may\nbe comparatively moderate, since the\nSAFE FIRST MORTGAGES\nREAPING THE FRUITS\nRELIEVED OF\nRESPONSIBILITY\nHere is one investment you\nwon't have to watch for a drop\nn 6% FIRST MORTGAGES\nI Over a Third\nr a continue 6% throughout\u2014and\nwith positive certainty that the\nCentury principal will be returned intact\nWithout a at the ex P iration of the term of\nthe mortgage.\nLoss\nMay be purchased in amounts\n.\u2018rom $250 up.\nB. F. SAUL CO.\nNational 2100 925 15th St. N.W.\nI THERE IS NO SUBSTITUTE FOR SAFETY\n11 1\nAnnouncing\nthe offering of\nSTAhuARD AMERICAN TRUST SHARES\nThese shares provide a single medium whereby investors may enjoy the\nbenefits of participation in the prosperity of America through diversified\ninvestment in twenty-five leading corporations. The portfolio of the trust\nconsists of the following common stocks, all of which are listed and actively\ntraded on the New York Stock Exchange:\nRAILROADS INDUSTRIALS\nAtchison, Topeka Allied Chemical Dye Corp.\nSanta Fe Ry. Co. American Can Co.\nCanadian Pacific Ry. Co. American Smelting Refining Co.\nNew York Central R. R. Co. American Tobacco Co. \"Class B\"\nUnion Pacific R. R. Co. Borden Company\nE. I. du Pont de Nemours Co.\ni a ri| T ir r Eastman Kodak Co. (of N. J.)\nUTILITIES General Electric Co.\nAmerican Telephone International Harvester Co.\nTelegraph Co. National Biscuit Co.\nColumbia Gas Electric Corp. Standard Oil Co. (N. J.)\nConsolidated Gas Co. of N. Y. Texas Corporation\nNorth American Co. Union Carbide Carbon Corp.\nPacific Gas Electric Co. United States Steel Corp,\nUnited Gas Improvement Co. Westinghouse Elec. A Mfg. Co.\nNo stocks other then these mey be held in the Trust except\nin the event of re-cepitellxatlon, merger, consolidation,\nsales of assets, or re-organixation by exchange of stock.\nStandard American Trust Shares represent equal undivided interests In a\ntrust of the fixed or non-discretionary type created pursuant to an agreement\nbetween Chicago Trust Company, as Trustee, and Standard American Cor\nporation, as Depositor.\nThe national distribution of these shares is sponsored by Lawrence Stern and\nCompany, the National Republic Company, investment affiliate of The\nNational Bank of the Republic of Chicago, Stein Bros. Boyce,\nand other banking institutions throughout the country.\nDescriptive circular upon request.\nThe National Republic Company. Lawrence Stern and Company\nChicago Chicago\nStein Bros. Boyce\nWoodwerd Bldg. Washington v\nSpring expansion wm disappointingly\n\u2022mall.\nOn the whole, however. Wall Street\nremained fairly confident of the ap\npearance of decisive signs of improve\nment by late Summer or early Autumn\nand some commentators pointed to the\nhistory of the past business recessions\nto back up these expectations. Bullish\noperations, nevertheless, were held in\nchecks by the fact that trading will b\nsuspended for the remainder of th\nweek at the end of 'Thursday\u2019s session\nover the Memorial day week end\nFurthermore, the market was still re\ngarded in conservative circles as work\ning within a comparatively narrov\ntrading area.\nA few of the more volatile issues\nmade wide gains. Allied Chemical anc\nPeople's Gas sold up about 10 point'\nand among issues gaining 4 points o:\nmore were Macy, Case. Autumn. Myers\nand Johns-Manville. North American\nLoew\u2019s, Eastman Kodak, United States\nSteel, American Can. Westinghouse Elec\ntric and Montgomery Ward rose 2 or\npoints.\nCHECK PAYMENTS.\nBy the Associated Press.\nCheck payments, as gauged by re\nports from leading centers of the Fed\neral Reserve system, declined 2 percent\nfor the week ended May 21 as compared\nwith the previous week. The total was\n23 per cent less than for the corre\nsponding week of 1929. Total for the\ncomparable periods follow:\nWeek ended May 21 $14,335,000,000\nPrevious week 14,546.000,000\nSame week last year.... 14,530,000.000\nNEW SECURITIES\nNEW YORK, May 26 OP).\u2014New se\ncurities offered today include:\nBrooklyn Union Gas Co., $18,000,000\n5 per cent debentures, offered at 102 Va\nand interest to yield 4.80 per cent, by\nNational City Co. and Guaranty Co.\nBANK CLEANINGS.\nNEW YORK. May 26 <Bpecial).\nN Y. bank clear- Today. A year aco\nin\u00bbs f 375.000.000 $579,000,000 1\nN. Y. bank bal-\nM n i es 134.000,000 105.000.000\nN. Y. Fed Res.\ncredit balances. 133.000.000 108,000.000\nWomen Sing at Execution.\nWhen Samuel Cushman was executed\nat Belfast, Ireland, recently, for the\nmurder of James McCann, a postman, a\ncrowd of women sang hymns outside\nthe prison. The prisoner\u2019s mother, who\nwas In the throng, fell in a swoon when\nthe hour of execution arrived.\nFINANCIAL.\nFifteen Years to Pay\n'J\u2019HE Real Estate Loan Plan of the\nMetropolitan Life Insurance Com\npany is developed to enable the home\nbuyer to pay small installments over\na number of years. It takes the bur\nden out of home owning.\nLet us explain the many advan\ntages of this widely accepted plan.\nConsult\n\nWEAVERBROC\nrealtors O\n809 15th St. N.W. District 9486\nMortgage Loan Correspondent\nMetropolitan Lite Insurance Company\nWe invite\napplications\nfor\nFirst\nMortgage\nLoans